52.7	Juliette_Binoche	Juliette Binoche	Juliette Binoche (French pronunciation: ; born 9 March 1964) is a French actress, artist and dancer. She has appeared in more than 40 feature films, been recipient of numerous international accolades, is a published author and has appeared on stage across the world. Coming from an artistic background, she began taking acting lessons during adolescence. After performing in several stage productions, she was propelled into the world of auteurs Jean-Luc Godard (Hail Mary, 1985), Jacques Doillon (Family Life, 1985) and André Téchiné, who made her a star in France with the leading role in his 1985 drama Rendez-vous. Her sensual performance in her English-language debut The Unbearable Lightness of Being (1988), directed by Philip Kaufman, launched her international career.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Movie_Juliette_Binoche_dans_les_Yeux.jpg/220px-Movie_Juliette_Binoche_dans_les_Yeux.jpg
